<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Jerry Hick; Doreen Carvajal, ; Bob Elston 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 HELPING HAND: Vietnamese in Orange County haven't forgotten the many others 
who still languish in camps throughout Southeast Asia. The Vietnamese 
Physicians Assn. of Southern California hosts a public meeting tonight with 
Werner Blatter, director of the United Nations refugees commission, at 
Westminster's civic center. . . . The association is pressing a proposal to 
close existing camps, allowing refugees up to 30 years old to emigrate to other 
countries. 
</P>
<P>
 NOAH'S RIDE: Racehorses have an assortment of unusual names. Like, Peter Noah. 
. . . TV producer Alan Kirschenbaum named his 3-year-old colt, which races at 
Los Alamitos, Peter Noah, after a close friend and fellow producer. Good 
friends, but competitors: Kirschenbaum's TV hit "Coach" duels with Noah's "Cafe 
Americain" on Tuesday nights. And the horse Peter Noah? He won his harness race 
last week at Los Alamitos' opening day, and is back again tonight. 
</P>
<P>
 JOINT HEROES: Judy Richardson was invited to speak at UC Irvine this week to 
help celebrate Martin Luther King Jr.'s birthday. But she hopes to shift 
attention to another African American leader of the 1960s -- Malcolm X. 
Richardson, a civil rights activist from that era, was an associate producer on 
the highly touted King documentary, "Eyes on the Prize." But she's just 
completed work on a new documentary on Malcolm X, to air Jan. 26 on public 
television's "American Experience." Says Richardson: "We started doing Malcolm 
three years ago, before Spike (Lee) did." 
</P>
<P>
 IN HOUSE: Two Democrats trying to climb the political ladder will be on hand 
when the Orange County Trial Lawyers Assn. installs new officers today. . . . 
State Treasurer Kathleen Brown, running for governor, will be speaking. And 
Assemblyman Tom Umberg of Garden Grove, running for attorney general, will be 
honored by the group, because he pioneered new probate legislation that 
restricts lawyers' control over their clients' estates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
