<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; PENNSYLVANIA; N.Y. SCHOOL REJECTS HARASSMENT SUSPECT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Swarthmore College freshman who agreed to attend another school at the 
college's expense because he was accused of harassing a female classmate was 
rejected from Columbia University.Ewart Yearwood, 18, was rejected "based on 
his academic record," a statement from university spokesman Fred Knubel said. 
Yearwood's departure from the Swarthmore, Pa., school came after another 
freshman, Alexis Clinansmith, 18, complained that he harassed her last 
semester. Yearwood denies the claims. 
