<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MOTORIST CHARGED IN FATAL ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 41-year-old Oxnard man has been arrested on felony drunk driving charges 
after he slammed his pickup truck into a disabled vehicle and killed a 
24-year-old Ventura man, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The accident occurred about 7:50 p.m. Wednesday on Vineyard Avenue north of 
Simon Way while Amanpreet Singh was pushing his Mitsubishi pickup truck in a 
southbound lane, the California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 Manuel Garcia was driving south on Vineyard at high speed when he struck 
Singh's pickup truck from behind, the CHP said. The impact killed Singh 
instantly and threw his body 120 feet. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia's pickup truck then spun into the northbound lanes and stopped. While 
Garcia was standing in the middle of the roadway, his pickup truck was struck 
by a vehicle driven by 29-year-old Matthew Paul Klasen of Fillmore. Klasen 
suffered minor injuries but was not taken to the hospital. 
</P>
<P>
 Garcia suffered minor injuries and was treated at St. John's Regional Medical 
Center and released into police custody. He was being held Thursday in Ventura 
County Jail on suspicion of felony drunk driving and vehicular manslaughter 
with gross negligence. His bail was set at $10,000. 
</P>
<P>
 Singh was driving to his job at a convenience store on Wooley Road in Oxnard 
when he was killed, said Deputy Coroner Zelmira Isaac. 
</P>
<P>
 A CHP spokesman said the agency is looking for witnesses to the accident to 
corroborate information gathered from physical evidence at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 CHP Officer Chris Day said he believes two youths between the ages of 13 and 
15 may have seen the accident. People with information should call Day at 
654-4571. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
