BRUIN WOMEN BEAT COUGARS, 108-76 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Natalie Williams scored 30 points and grabbed 10 rebounds as UCLA routed 
Washington State, 108-76, on Thursday night before 364 at Pauley Pavilion. 
</P>
<P>
 Williams has scored 20 points or more and has had 10 or more rebounds in nine 
of the Bruins' 12 games. 
</P>
<P>
 Amy Jalewalia had 13 points, Taniko Hilbert 11, and Zrinka Kristich and 
Allison Arredondo 10 apiece in helping UCLA improve to 7-5 overall and 2-1 in 
the Pacific 10 Conference. The Bruins shot a season-high 54.3%. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cougars (6-6, 1-2) were led by Jenni Rouff with 19 points. 
