<HEADLINE>
<P>
KERRIGAN MIGHT SKATE THE WEEK BEFORE OLYMPICS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LARRY STEWART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 If she is physically able to skate, Nancy Kerrigan will make her return to the 
ice in an exhibition at Boston College the week before the Winter Olympics 
begin on Feb. 12, CBS announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Rick Gentile, the network's senior vice president of production, said the 
exact date has not been set, but CBS will televise the exhibition in prime 
time, probably on a one-day tape delay.He guessed it would be after Feb. 4. 
</P>
<P>
 The women's skating competition at the Olympics in Lillehammer, Norway, is 
scheduled for Feb. 23 and 25.  
</P>
<P>
 Gentile said Kerrigan will first have to be cleared to skate by the U.S. 
Figure Skating Assn. He said arrangements for the exhibition were made through 
ProServ, the agency that represents Kerrigan, and that other skaters will also 
take part. 
</P>
<P>
 An unspecified rights fee was paid to ProServ, according to Gentile. LARRY 
STEWART 
</P>
</TEXT>
