<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' ROUNDUP; PACIFICA ENDS KENNEDY'S STREAK AT 37 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kennedy's 37-game Garden Grove League winning streak ended Thursday night with 
a 95-81 loss to a Pacifica team that was a good as advertised. But afterward, 
the visiting Fighting Irish weren't conceding anything to the fifth-ranked 
Mariners. 
</P>
<P>
 "Any team can be beaten on any given night," Kennedy senior guard Wes Morris 
said. "They just happened to be the better team tonight." 
</P>
<P>
 Pacifica was certainly the deeper team and the better perimeter-shooting team. 
The Mariners came at Kennedy in waves as Pacifica Coach Bob Becker used 11 
players liberally. The Mariners led, 45-44, at halftime, but wore down Kennedy 
in the second half with their size and their relentless three-point shooting 
attack. 
</P>
<P>
 Ryan Teague (19 points, four three-pointers) broke the game open by hitting 
two three-pointers from the corner in Pacifica's 13-0 run that opened the 
second half. 
</P>
<P>
 "That's one of my favorite shots to shoot on the floor," Teague said. "I just 
thank my teammates for getting me the ball and God for letting the ball go in." 
</P>
<P>
 Said Kennedy Coach John Mayberry: "It's funny because at halftime I told our 
team to watch out for 30 (Teague) and 54 (Chris Vlasic)." 
</P>
<P>
 Vlasic did much of his damage after halftime too. Saddled with three fouls in 
the first half, Vlasic scored 11 of his 19 points after halftime and also 
grabbed six of his nine rebounds after intermission. 
</P>
<P>
 The Fighting Irish (5-10, 3-1 in league) closed to within five points twice in 
the fourth quarter, but every time they got close Pacifica (13-1, 4-0) would 
usually counter with a three-pointer. 
</P>
<P>
 "They can shoot, and they don't stop shooting," Mayberry said. 
</P>
<P>
 Still, Morris (18 points, six steals) wasn't convinced of anything. 
</P>
<P>
 "They outplayed us, but I just can't wait to play them again," he said. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Academy League: 
</P>
<P>
 St. Margaret's 88, Vista Cal Lutheran 30 -- Damian Raibon scored 16 points to 
lead three St. Margaret's players in double figures. St. Margaret's is 10-3, 
2-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Metro League: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific Shores 54, Colton Christian Center Academy 53 -- Josh Kalb scored a 
layup with eight seconds left to give host Pacific Shores the victory. Kalb had 
a team-high 15 points for Pacific Shores (5-4, 3-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
