<P>
PREP SOCCER ROUNDUP; FOURTH-RANKED EL MODENA RALLIES TO TOP CANYON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAN ARRITT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fourth-ranked El Modena fell behind early, but rallied for a 2-1 victory over 
Canyon in a Century League girls' soccer game Thursday at Canyon High. 
</P>
<P>
 The Vanguards (12-4, 3-0 in league) moved a game ahead of Canyon (9-4-1, 2-1), 
which has won two consecutive league titles and five of the last seven. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon dominated most of the game, but El Modena took advantage of its scoring 
chances. 
</P>
<P>
 After Canyon's Laura Flatauer beat Vanguard goalkeeper Amy Moreno to the ball 
and scored 15 minutes into the game, Laurie Zemke answered just before halftime 
with her first goal of the year. 
</P>
<P>
 Canyon kept pressure on El Modena for most of the second half, but Moreno was 
up to each challenge and was credited with eight saves. 
</P>
<P>
 With 10 minutes remaining, Stephanie Esparza found Aja Cordova open in front 
of the goal, and Cordova headed the soft pass into the net for the winning 
goal. 
</P>
<P>
 "I felt we had control and momentum coming out of halftime," El Modena Coach 
Tino Younger said. "And I felt confident we could get another score in the 
second half." DAN ARRITT 
</P>
