<HEADLINE>
<P>
CAPISTRANO VALLEY PLAYER REMAINS HOSPITALIZED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DAVE McKIBBEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Capistrano Valley goalkeeper Jason Felix, who was knocked unconscious after 
being kneed in the head during Wednesday's game against Mission Viejo, remained 
hospitalized Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 His mother, Priscilla, aid there was no damage to her son's head, but she said 
he did suffer bruises to his spinal cord. 
</P>
<P>
 "A knee hit him in the cheek or neck and that caused a whiplash," Priscilla 
Felix said. 
</P>
<P>
 Felix underwent an MRI Thursday night to see if his vertebrae or disk had been 
moved. Priscilla Felix said her son will remain in Mission Hospital Regional 
Medical Center until at least today until results of the MRI are available. 
