<P>
YOSHIZUMI LEADS ANTEATER SWIMMERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gwen Yoshizumi won two events to help UC Irvine to victories against San Jose 
State and Loyola Marymount in women's nonconference swimming and diving meets 
Thursday at UC Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
 UC Irvine beat San Jose State, 122-111, and Loyola Marymount, 137-56. 
Yoshizumi won the 100 freestyle in 56.06 and the 200 freestyle (2:01.41). 
</P>
<P>
 Janelle Wong won the 50 freestyle (26.16) also for Irvine. The Anteaters' Kara 
Anderson won the one-meter diving with 189 points teammate April Gibbs won the 
three-meter diving (202.30). 
