<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. PREMIERE OF 'ALTMAN' TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 "Luck, Trust & Ketchup: Robert Altman in Carver Country," a feature-length 
documentary about the evolution and making of Altman's film "Short Cuts," will 
have its Los Angeles premiere tonight at the EZTV Arts Foundation in West 
Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 The premiere, with screenings at 7 and 9:15 p.m., will benefit the arts 
organization, which is located at 8547 Santa Monica Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 The documentary reveals Altman's legendary "improvisational technique," 
focusing on his interactions with the all-star cast during "Short Cuts' " 
10-week shoot. 
</P>
<P>
 The documentary was created by producer-director Mike Kaplan and the late John 
Dorr, EZTV's founder. Information: (310) 823-4024. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA011494-0183 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 003995 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
January 14, 1994, Friday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Calendar; Part F; Page 20; Column 2; Entertainment Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
