<HEADLINE>
<P>
PEOPLE: LIEBHOLD TO FILL TECHNOLOGY POST AT TIMES MIRROR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Michael Liebhold, formerly a scientist for Apple Computer Inc., has been named 
to the new post of vice president of technology at Times Mirror Co., The Times' 
parent company announced Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Liebhold, 49, will be responsible for guiding Times Mirror's efforts to apply 
new technologies to a broad variety of its businesses. He will also advise the 
company on acquisitions and strategic alliances and will represent Times Mirror 
on various technology issues. 
</P>
<P>
 He will report to Efrem Zimbalist III, vice president for strategic 
development. 
</P>
<P>
 At Apple, Liebhold was a senior scientist in media architectures research. His 
team made fundamental contributions to the development of Quicktime, Apple's 
media software architecture for the Macintosh, Windows and Unix operating 
systems. 
</P>
