</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 New York Investigates Prudential Insurance: Regulators said they are 
investigating the company for selling group annuity contracts that were never 
approved by the state. A Prudential spokesman said similar violations could 
have occurred in other states.He said the company is conducting its own 
internal review. A spokesman for the New York state insurance department said 
the unauthorized group contracts affected thousands of individuals. In a 
related development, federal prosecutors investigating fraud at Prudential 
Securities have issued subpoenas to former and current executives of the firm, 
according to a published report. Prosecutors have expanded their investigation 
into sales of VMS Mortgage Investment, one of the biggest limited partnerships 
offered by Prudential. Prosecutors had focused on sales of $1.3 billion in 
Prudential-Bache Energy Income partnerships to 130,000 people. 
</P>
