<HEADLINE>
<P>
EXECUTIVE SUITE: POLYGRAM FILM DIVISION NAMES EXECUTIVE VP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rick Finkelstein has been named executive vice president of Polygram Filmed 
Entertainment, overseeing the company's business affairs and legal activities 
in the United States. He will report to Michael Kuhn, president of the company, 
a division of London-based Polygram.Finkelstein previously worked as a 
consultant to Polygram Filmed Entertainment, where he helped negotiate key 
financing and distribution agreements. 
</P>
<P>
 MCA Records named Beth Halper and Kelley Walker A&R representatives. 
</P>
<P>
 Chicago-based regional telephone giant Ameritech named former Columbia Tristar 
Home Video executive W. Patrick Campbell executive vice president of corporate 
strategy and business development. His duties will include developing video and 
wireless communication services. 
</P>
<P>
 David Palmer is the new director of marketing, domestic licensing and 
merchandising for Turner Home Entertainment. 
</P>
<P>
 Steven T. Florio was named president of Conde Nast Publications Inc. USA by 
Chairman S.I. Newhouse Jr. He succeeds Bernard Leser, who has been named Conde 
Nast's chairman of Pacific operations. 
</P>
<P>
 Patrick Quigley was named senior vice president of marketing for EMI Records 
Group, North America. 
</P>
<P>
 Bank of America has promoted its chief entertainment lender, Laura L. Calhoun, 
to senior vice president. 
</P>
<P>
 Fox Inc. has named Bruce B. Churchill senior vice president of finance, 
overseeing accounting, tax and treasury activities. 
</P>
<P>
 Rhino Records has named Andrea Kinloch product manager. 
</P>
<P>
 ITC Entertainment Group has named Valerie R. Randolph director of business and 
legal affairs. 
</P>
<P>
 Walt Disney Co. has promoted T.J. Baptie to vice president of corporate 
relations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
