<P>
BRIEFCASE: MEDIA AND MARKETING; UNCOVERING MAGAZINE'S BLUFF ABOUT FEATURING 
SOCIETY EDITOR IN THE BUFF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Anne Michaud, Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange Coast magazine promised that its January issue would depict a local 
personality with clothes off. But those who considered that a promise of nudity 
were too hasty, said the magazine's publisher, Ruth Ko. 
</P>
<P>
 The new issue shows Carol Humphreys, society editor for the Orange County 
Register, with clothes off -- but bathing suit on. In an accompanying article, 
Humphreys discusses such weighty topics as her favorite time of day. (It's 
sunset.) 
</P>
<P>
 Ko said the feature is an attempt to highlight people's sensuous -- and not 
necessarily sexual -- facets. "There are enough photos of Marion Bergeson or 
Kathryn Thompson behind a desk," she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Said Humphreys: "I had to think about it first; but it was fun, and I thought 
it was tastefully done." 
</P>
<P>
 Who's up for February? Ko is not saying. You'll have to buy the magazine, she 
said, which is exactly the point. 
</P>
