TOKOS MEDICAL TO LAY OFF 200 WORKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tokos Medical Corp. plans to consolidate centers providing certain services 
and lay off 200 employees nationwide, although the job losses in Orange County 
will be offset by gains in other areas, executives said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
 Tokos plans to consolidate its telemedical services, in which staff members 
speak directly with patients to educate them about the company's products. It 
also plans to eliminate its manufacturing operations and contract out that 
work. 
</P>
<P>
 The job losses in those areas will be offset in Orange County by bringing 
people from other units to the company's Santa Ana headquarters, said chief 
financial officer Nicholas A. Mione. Nationwide, the 200 positions being 
eliminated represent about 10% of the company's total work force. 
