ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; MAN IS HELD AFTER ARGUMENT, STABBING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man was arrested Thursday on suspicion of stabbing a friend during an 
argument, police said. The latter was not seriously hurt. 
</P>
<P>
 Duane Kyle Terry, 23, was arguing with Dennis Dodier, 30, both of Westminster, 
in the 7200 block of Wyoming Street about 1:25 p.m. Thursday, Lt. Mike Chliskey 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dodier then started to choke Terry, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 "They had been friends, but the one being choked . . . pulled out a 
pocketknife and stabbed the other one three times in the back and one time in 
the neck," Chliskey said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dodier got away, ran outside and called police officers, who were in the area 
on a separate investigation, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Dodier was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange for treatment of superficial 
knife wounds and later released, Chliskey said. 
</P>
<P>
 Terry was being held at Orange County Jail. 
