<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: TRABUCO CANYON; MAN PLEADS GUILTY TO MOLESTING 4 GIRLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RENE LYNCH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A former stable handyman pleaded guilty Thursday to molesting four young girls 
and faces a possible six years in prison when he is sentenced later this month, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said Ray Rowe, 48, of Trabuco Canyon befriended the girls' 
families and then molested the young girls when alone with them. 
</P>
<P>
 Deputy Dist. Atty. Nancy du Pont said Rowe was originally charged with two 
felony counts of lewd conduct with a child and two misdemeanor counts of child 
molestation involving two girls. 
</P>
<P>
 After further review, the misdemeanor charges were upgraded to felonies, and 
two new misdemeanor molestation charges were added when two more victims came 
forward, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 All four girls are younger than 14, du Pont said. Deputy Public Defender Marri 
Derby, who is representing Rowe, could not be reached for comment late 
Thursday. Rowe is scheduled to be sentenced Jan. 27 in Laguna Niguel Municipal 
Court. 
</P>
<P>
 The first molestation took place in Tustin in 1991 and involved a 12-year-old 
girl. Rowe persuaded the girl's parents to let him take her fishing, and 
molested her during the trip, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 A complaint was made to the Orange County Sheriff's Department at that time, 
but no action was taken due to insufficient evidence, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rowe was arrested after a second girl alleged that he molested her in 1993 
while visiting a Trabuco Canyon area stable to ride horses, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 In that incident, Rowe undressed and forced the girl to fondle him, and also 
molested her, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said two more girls came forward after learning about the arrest. 
RENE LYNCH 
</P>
</TEXT>
