<P>
 Umberg vote -- A story Wednesday about legislative committee action on a child 
pornography bill mischaracterized the position of Assemblyman Tom Umberg 
(D-Garden Grove). Umberg abstained from voting last April because of 
ambiguities now resolved, spokesman George Urch said, and he now supports the 
bill -- including felony provisions. 
